	&lt;h2&gt;
		How To Measure&lt;/h2&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;
		Obtain an accurate height measurement from the ground to the tallest part of the withers while horse is standing squarely.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;
		Using a flexible tape or piece of rope take a total heart girth measurement. This is the total circumference of the chest, in a vertical line just behind the shoulders over the withers.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;
		Refer to the chart for the correct suit sizing, Suits are sold in half-hands with three fits available; Standard, Mid, and Max.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;/image/data/infomartion/How-To-See-The-Fitting-Chart.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
";}i:49;a:7:{s:14:"information_id";s:1:"3";s:6:"bottom";s:1:"1";s:10:"sort_order";s:1:"1";s:6:"status";s:1:"1";s:11:"language_id";s:1:"1";s:5:"title";s:10:"Why Hidez?";s:11:"description";s:3142:"&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;Hidez animal compression suits are engineered using&amp;nbsp;inovative technology. The panels are designed, cut and sewn to focus on muscle groups. The unique design creates a controlled graduated compression to an animal&amp;rsquo;s body.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;color: red&quot;&gt;Recovery:&lt;/strong&gt; Graduated compression means that a greater amount of pressure is applied at the extremities (the lowest point of the leg) and the pressure reduces along the limbs and body. The technique employed by the design of Hidez animal compression suits assists in forcing vital blood supplies out of the lower limbs, back into circulation and towards the heart. This process may enhance blood flow and oxygen available to an animal&amp;rsquo;s muscles.&amp;nbsp; In addition, the process can speed up the removal of waste products like lactic acids and carbon dioxide, for vital blood supplies. Good healthy blood supplies ensures recovery from injuries faster, helps in the prevention of injuries by maintaining muscle temperature and reduces muscle fatigue by flushing out &amp;lsquo;bad blood&amp;rsquo;, which aids in the reduction of delayed onset muscle soreness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;color: red&quot;&gt;Travel:&lt;/strong&gt; Just like human graduated compression apparel brands, Hidez animal compression suits use a unique muscle focus design when applying pressure to an animal&amp;rsquo;s hide. The suit wraps the muscle groups focusing on controlling graduated compression, but also aiding in the reduction of muscle vibrations. This is very important when animals are travelling. Muscle&amp;rsquo;s work extremely hard during travelling, they vibrate &amp;amp; can overstretch. Muscle vibration can cause micro fibres to tear in the muscles, as a result membranes leak and the enzyme Creatine Kinase (CK) leaks into the blood in high concentrations causing cramping and ultimately travel sickness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;color: red&quot;&gt;Fabric: &lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;Hidez manufactures its own fabric with superior&amp;nbsp;breathability and moisture management properties&amp;nbsp;in a high stretch elastomeric yarn&amp;nbsp;. This fabric is made using a &amp;quot;warp knit&amp;quot; construction. Warp knitted fabrics are more durable than regular circular knitted fabrics.Our fabric is among the most durable fabrics of&amp;nbsp;this kind anywhere in the world and designed to return its natural / original shape no matter how much physical exertion or force the fabrics have been put under when worn&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/Contact-Hidez.html&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;For more information about the Hidez animal compression suit please contact us&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
";}}